{
  "texts": [
    "While BERT often achieves higher performance (as shown in Table 2), it is too slow for many practical use cases.",
    "On the other hand, SBERT has appropriate performance on the practical side, but requires in-domain training data and fine-tuning over the target task to achieve competitive performance (Thakur et al., 2020).",
    "In this study, SBERT was used for calculating p2p similarity.",
    "The most important advantage of using SBERT is that a practical infrastructure for calculating p2p similarity with the performance of BERT can be proposed.",
    "Table 2: Evaluation BERT and SBERT on the STS benchmark test set (Reimers and Gurevych, 2019)"
  ]
}